signatures.note:
Quire marks are written in the upper margin of the following
                                 leaves:
 3r: ፩ “1”;
 12r: ፪ “2”; 
 21r: ፫ “3”; 
 29r: ፬
                                 “4”;
 37r: ፭ “5”;
 44r: ፮ “6”;
 52r: ፯ “7”.

handDesc.handNote:
                        Careful.
                        Black; red.
                        The
                        concluding supplication formula (54ra)
                        mentions ʾabuna Gabra Krǝstos as the scribe (different from the scribe of
                        QSM-023 and FBM-001).19th century


ሰላ፡ for ሰላም፡ on 50va, l.16; 50vb,
                              l.8; 51ra, ls. 1, 10; 51rb, ls. 1, 10; 51va, ls. 2, 11; 52ra, ls. 4,
                              11; 52rb, ls. 1, 10; 52va, ls. 2, 10; 52vb, ls. 1, 9, 17; 53ra, ls.
                              6-7, 13-14; 53rb, ls. 5, 13; 53va, ls. 6, 15; 53vb, l.7.

ዮሐ፡ for ዮሐንስ፡ on 52vb, ls. 5, 13;
                              53ra, ls. 3, 10; 53va, l.1; 53vb, l.2.

ዮሐን፡ for ዮሐንስ፡ on 53rb, ls. 1, 10,
                              53va, l.10.

                        Nomina sacra; 
 six lines in both columns of the
                           incipit page (fol. 3r), divided into three groups, alterning with black
                           lines;
 four lines divided into two groups, alterning with black
                           lines, in both columns of fols. 25r and 30r (beginning of Text II);
                           three groups of two/three lines on fol. 42r (beginning of Text III);
                           the beginning two lines of each miracle within Text III;
 the first
                           two lines of Text IV;
 the horizontal dashes above and below Ethiopic
                           numerals; 
 elements of the punctuation signs;
 the word salām
